You know those dashboards that get built, presented, and then never looked at again?

Yeah‚Ä¶ this isn't one of those roles.

3+ years in digital analytics, ideally within a large, data-heavy environment (telco, finance, or consulting would be perfect)

You know your way around GA4 (Google Analytics), Looker Studio, and digital tracking implementations

You speak fluent SQL, and you're comfortable in BigQuery or similar

You've built dashboards in Tableau or Power BI that didn't just look good - they changed behaviour

You're proactive, collaborative, and not afraid to challenge the brief

Why You'll Love It

You won't just analyse data - you'll influence what happens next.

You'll work with a team that values curiosity over compliance, collaboration over control, and insights over outputs.

It's a role with meaning - using analytics to protect customers, improve experiences, and make data genuinely matter.

SkyCity Adelaide is seeking a strategic and data-driven Customer Insights and Strategy Manager to lead our customer analytics function. This pivotal role is central to our strategy of leveraging customer data to drive profitable growth across our casino, hotel, and F&B offerings.

Reporting directly to the Head of Insights and Loyalty, you will be responsible for leading a team of analysts to transform complex customer data into actionable commercial strategies. You will own the end-to-end customer data strategy, from deep-dive analysis to predictive modelling, to inform our loyalty program, marketing campaigns, and overall customer experience.

Key to your success will be your ability to provide a holistic view of the customer journey. This involves synthesizing data from our casino loyalty program (including player preferences and rated play), hotel occupancy, and F&B spend to develop a unified customer value proposition and deliver a superior return on investment.

Key Accountabilities

Lead, mentor, and develop a team of two analysts, setting the strategic direction for the customer insights function.
Synthesize data from casino (table games, EGMs, eTG), hotel, and F&B systems to provide a 360-degree view of customer behaviour and value.
Develop and monitor key casino performance metrics, working closely with Gaming Analysts to optimize player rating and operational efficiency.
Partner with the Hotel Revenue Manager to strategically utilize hotel inventory as a lever to drive casino visitation and profitability.
Design and measure the effectiveness of all marketing promotions and campaigns, providing data-driven recommendations for optimization.
Own the strategic development and business case for our loyalty program, ensuring it effectively acquires, retains, and grows high-value customers.
Deliver compelling presentations, reports, and ad-hoc analyses that tell a meaningful story and influence senior leadership in strategic decision-making.

About you

To be successful in this role, you will be an established leader with a proven track record in a complex, customer-centric environment, ideally within the casino, gaming, or integrated resort industry.

You possess a unique blend of deep analytical expertise, strong business acumen, and the leadership skills to guide a team and influence stakeholders. You are as comfortable diving into the data as you are presenting its strategic implications to the C-suite.

Essential Experience and Skills:

A minimum of 8 years of experience in customer/data analytics, with at least 5 years in a direct people-management role leading teams responsible for data analysis, loyalty program design, and campaign planning.
Demonstrable experience in the casino/gaming industry, with a strong understanding of: casino loyalty programs and member acquisition strategies, player tracking systems and the mechanics of rating play across table games, EGMs, and eTGs, and key casino performance indicators (e.g., Hold, Theo, ADT).
Proven ability to analyse and interpret data from multiple sources (casino, hotel, F&B) to form holistic business recommendations.
Hands-on experience with analytical programming languages (e.g., SAS, R, Python, SQL) with the ability to guide and mentor a technical team.
A strong commercial mindset, with the ability to consider factors beyond the raw data‚Äîsuch as operational feasibility and customer sentiment‚Äîwhen forming strategies.
Exceptional communication skills, with a talent for distilling complex data into clear, actionable insights via PowerPoint, Excel, and executive-level write-ups.
A degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Marketing, Management, Engineering, Computer Science, or a related quantitative field.

Highly Advantageous:

Experience in predictive analytics and modelling (e.g., churn prediction, lifetime value forecasting).
Experience working in or closely with hotel revenue management.

What's in it for you?

Besides working with great people and getting firsthand experience of SkyCity's newest entertainment offerings, you will also be rewarded with a range of employee benefits including;

Free employee meals available at our employee restaurant.
In-house dry-cleaning service, which is also available for personal use at a discounted rate.
Subsidised car parking and public transport tickets.
Discounts available across SkyCity Adelaide venues.
Free flu vaccinations, skins checks and other health checks.
Employee reward and recognition programmes.
Fantastic career and professional development opportunities.

If this sounds like the next role for you, please apply online today!

No recruitment agencies please.

At SkyCity, our career opportunities are as diverse as our workforce. We don't just embrace differences; we value and support them. Our hiring is centred on capability and performance, regardless of gender, gender identity, race, origin, age, educational background, disability, or religious beliefs. We're here to empower you to shine. Our willingness to adapt ensures you can chart your path with us! Join us at SkyCity and be extraordinary by being you.

Job Description

At Canva, our mission is to empower the world to design. To ensure our generative AI models are truly helpful, we are seeking a talented Research Engineer to build the foundational datasets and systems that fuel our next-generation generative AI models and evaluation capabilities.

About the role:

In this foundational role, you will be the expert on what truly fuels our models: data. You'll own the end-to-end lifecycle of our critical datasets, from curating nuanced human feedback on design quality to pioneering machine learning for high-quality synthetic data generation. This unique position calls for a data-first thinker with a strong design sensibility, passionate about building the high-quality ground truth at scale that will define the future of creativity by ensuring our models align with human taste and intent.

At the moment, this role is focused on:

Statistical Analysis & Insights: Applying robust statistical methodologies to analyze data, identify significant trends, and derive actionable insights. This includes hypothesis testing, regression analysis, and determining statistical significance to validate model performance and user preferences.

Human Feedback Data Curation: Owning the design, processing, cleaning, and strategic curation of large-scale, subjective human feedback on design quality, which is the lifeblood of our models.

Synthetic Data Generation: Using generative AI and machine learning techniques to create novel, high-quality synthetic data that augments our training sets and improves model capabilities.

Alignment Analysis & Evaluation Design: Designing methods to analyze outputs from both human and automated systems to deeply understand and measure our models' alignment with user preferences.

Primary Responsibilities:

Design and build scalable pipelines for processing and curating large datasets of human design feedback.

Research and develop ML models to generate high-quality synthetic data for training and fine-tuning.

Own the design and implementation of human evaluation workflows, including creating guidelines and quality rubrics.

Prepare datasets for automated evaluation systems and conduct deep analysis of their outputs to provide robust signals on model performance and human alignment.

Design and analyze experiments to measure the real-world impact of our models on design quality.

Conduct deep-dive analyses into model performance to identify failure modes and guide future development.

You‚Äôre probably a match if you have:

A strong aesthetic sense, with a background or demonstrated passion for visual design or human-computer interaction.

Strong proficiency in Python and ML frameworks (e.g., PyTorch, TensorFlow).

Extensive experience with designing and implementing large-scale data processing workflows using libraries like Pandas and data warehousing solutions such as Snowflake.

Solid understanding of statistical methods, including experimental design, A/B testing, and quality evaluation systems.

Experience with generative AI and synthetic data generation is highly desirable.

Nice to have:

Experience with cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, GCP, Azure) for data storage, processing, and MLOps related to dataset management.

Experience with MLOps practices and tools specifically for data versioning, lineage, and pipeline automation.

Ability to develop data visualization or data collection interfaces (e.g., TypeScript, Python).

Additional Information

At Canva, we know that great engineers come from a variety of backgrounds, and we value passion, curiosity, and a willingness to learn just as much as specific experience.
